{
  "text": "+ subfractions, including CD38 + or \u2212 and ckit high/low/\u2212 cells, in 96-well plates precoated with a murine stromal cell line (MS- 5 27 ), instead of allogeneic BM stromal cells, as reported elsewhere. [CITATION_1] In brief, MS-5 stromal cells were maintained in \u2423-medium supplemented with 10% FCS. For coculture with enriched human progenitors, unirradiated MS-5 feeders were established in 96-well plates (3 \u00d7 10 3 cells/well). To avoid early detachment of the stromal layer, we used gelatin-coated plates (MS-0096G, Sumitomo Bakelite, Tokyo, Japan). In these limiting dilution experiments, each CD34 + subfraction was seeded at four different initial cell concentrations (from 2 to 100 cells/well), using a mean of 40 \u00b1 8 replicate wells for two to 10 cells and 28 \u00b1 7 wells for 20 to 100 cells.",
